<div type="definition">
<p>SHAPE WHICH HAS LENGTH BUT LACKS OR HAS INTENSELY LITTLE BREADTH.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. Shéng 繩 is the abstract term for a line is the word for the thread/rope, used figuratively, often expanded to shéng mò 繩墨 "the inkline".</p>
<p>2. Háng 行 refers specificallty to a line of text. MOVE THIS TO LINE-OF-WRITING</p>
<p>3. Jìng 徑 refers specifically to the line constituted by a diameter of a circle.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
